---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';

const githubUrl = 'https://github.com/maxistar/Voice-Inbox';
const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL.replace(/\/$/, '');
const testingUrl = `${base}/testing/`;
const androidScreenshot = `${base}/screenshots/android-main.jpg`;
---
<Layout
  title="Voice notes to Markdown"
  description="Voice Inbox is a local-first app for turning accumulated voice recordings into a Markdown or plain-text inbox. Android is ready; iOS is an active MVP."
>
  <style>
    .hero {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: minmax(0, 1.05fr) minmax(280px, 0.75fr);
      gap: 42px;
      align-items: center;
      min-height: 560px;
    }
    .hero-copy p {
      max-width: 640px;
      font-size: 1.12rem;
    }
    .hero-visual {
      border: 1px solid var(--border);
      border-radius: 28px;
      background: linear-gradient(180deg, #eff6ff, #ffffff);
      box-shadow: var(--shadow);
      padding: 18px;
    }
    .screenshot-shell {
      border: 10px solid #111827;
      border-radius: 28px;
      background: #f8fafc;
      overflow: hidden;
      max-height: 620px;
    }
    .screenshot-shell img {
      display: block;
      width: 100%;
      height: auto;
    }
    .caption {
      margin: 14px 0 0;
      color: var(--soft);
      font-size: 0.9rem;
      text-align: center;
    }
    .platform-card {
      display: grid;
      gap: 12px;
    }
    .status-badge {
      display: inline-flex;
      width: fit-content;
      border-radius: 999px;
      padding: 5px 10px;
      color: var(--accent-strong);
      background: var(--accent-soft);
      font-size: 0.78rem;
      font-weight: 850;
    }
    .flow {
      counter-reset: flow;
    }
    .flow .card {
      position: relative;
      padding-left: 58px;
    }
    .flow .card::before {
      counter-increment: flow;
      content: counter(flow);
      position: absolute;
      left: 20px;
      top: 22px;
      width: 26px;
      height: 26px;
      border-radius: 8px;
      color: white;
      background: var(--accent);
      display: grid;
      place-items: center;
      font-weight: 900;
    }
    .requirements {
      border: 1px solid var(--border);
      border-radius: 8px;
      background: var(--surface);
      padding: 24px;
    }
    @media (max-width: 860px) {
      .hero {
        grid-template-columns: 1fr;
        min-height: auto;
      }
    }
  </style>

  <section class="hero">
    <div class="hero-copy">
      <p class="eyebrow">Local-first voice note transcription</p>
      <h1>Turn voice notes into a Markdown inbox.</h1>
      <p>
        Voice Inbox turns accumulated recordings into a readable text inbox. Android has the mature
        task-list workflow today; iOS now has an active MVP for importing, previewing, transcribing,
        and appending individual recordings locally.
      </p>
      <div class="button-row">
        <a class="button primary" href={testingUrl}>Join Android closed test</a>
        <a class="button" href={`${base}/setup/`}>Setup guide</a>
        <a class="button" href={githubUrl} target="_blank" rel="noopener">View source</a>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="hero-visual" aria-label="Voice Inbox app preview">
      <div class="screenshot-shell">
        <img src={androidScreenshot} alt="Voice Inbox Android app showing scanned audio files and playback actions" />
      </div>
      <p class="caption">Android workflow screenshot. iOS MVP is evolving alongside the shared core.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <p class="eyebrow">Platform status</p>
    <h2>Android is in closed testing; iOS is catching up fast.</h2>
    <div class="grid">
      <div class="card platform-card">
        <span class="status-badge">Android closed test</span>
        <h3>Flexible task workflow</h3>
        <p>Import or receive individual recordings, optionally scan a selected audio folder, preview tasks, transcribe one file or a batch, retry failures, and schedule best-effort background runs.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card platform-card">
        <span class="status-badge">iOS MVP</span>
        <h3>Manual import workflow</h3>
        <p>Import audio files, preview them, download the speech model, transcribe locally, show recognized text, and append output. Folder automation and scheduling are still in progress.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card platform-card">
        <span class="status-badge">Shared core</span>
        <h3>Kotlin Multiplatform foundation</h3>
        <p>Catalog and transcription use cases are moving into shared code so Android and iOS can converge without hiding platform-specific storage and background limitations.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <p class="eyebrow">What it does</p>
    <h2>Built for accumulated recordings, not live dictation.</h2>
    <div class="grid">
      <div class="card">
        <h3>Individual or folder transcription</h3>
        <p>Import or share individual recordings, or optionally select one folder and process only files that are new or changed.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <h3>Local recognition</h3>
        <p>Download the model or install it from a compatible local folder. After installation, recognition runs on device instead of sending audio to an app cloud service.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <h3>Markdown or plain text output</h3>
        <p>Create a new <code>.md</code> or <code>.txt</code> document, or choose an existing writable file. Each successful note is appended without replacing earlier content.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <h3>Preview before processing</h3>
        <p>Play audio files from the list before deciding to transcribe them.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <h3>Scheduled processing</h3>
        <p>On Android, optionally ask the app to run scheduled transcription around your chosen time. Exact execution is not guaranteed.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <h3>Transparent history</h3>
        <p>Processed and failed files stay visible, and failed files can be retried individually.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <p class="eyebrow">Workflow</p>
    <h2>From recordings to notes in five steps.</h2>
    <div class="grid flow">
      <div class="card"><h3>Install the model</h3><p>Download and verify the model, or install it from a compatible local folder.</p></div>
      <div class="card"><h3>Prepare output</h3><p>Create or choose a writable Markdown or text document.</p></div>
      <div class="card"><h3>Add recordings</h3><p>Import files, share audio to Voice Inbox, or optionally select an audio folder.</p></div>
      <div class="card"><h3>Review tasks</h3><p>Preview recordings and check what is ready to process.</p></div>
      <div class="card"><h3>Transcribe</h3><p>Append one entry per successful file with filename, recording time, and recognized text.</p></div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section requirements">
    <p class="eyebrow">Requirements</p>
    <h2>Designed for local, on-device recognition.</h2>
    <p>
      Android requires Android 7.0 (API 24) or later on an ARM64 device. Both Android and the iOS MVP
      need network access for the first model download and enough free storage for model installation.
    </p>
    <div class="button-row">
      <a class="button primary" href={testingUrl}>Join Android closed test</a>
      <a class="button" href={`${base}/faq/`}>Read FAQ</a>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
